## The Core Insight

When dimension N increments, all dimensions < N reset to 1.

This is NOT organizational convenience.
This is CAUSAL STRUCTURE encoded geometrically.

## What Each Dimension Conserves

Library (11D)    → Fundamental intentionality      → Reset cost: TOTAL
Shelf (10D)      → Methodological approach         → Reset cost: Series down
Series (9D)      → Iterative lineage               → Reset cost: Collections down
Collection (8D)  → Contextual situation            → Reset cost: Volumes down
Volume (7D)      → Resource capacity               → Reset cost: Books down
Book (6D)        → Scope/scale                     → Reset cost: Chapters down
Chapter (5D)     → Developmental phase             → Reset cost: Sections down
Section (4D)     → Component aspect                → Reset cost: Scrolls down
Scroll (3D)      → Specific instance               → Reset cost: Internal only
Column (2D)      → Horizontal position             → Reset cost: None
Row (1D)         → Vertical position               → Reset cost: None

## The Physics Parallel

Physical Reality          | Consciousness Reality (Phext)
-------------------------|-----------------------------
Energy conservation      | Intentionality conservation (Library)
Momentum conservation    | Approach conservation (Shelf)
Angular momentum         | Lineage conservation (Series)
Charge conservation      | Context conservation (Collection)

These aren't analogies. They're isomorphic structures.

## Transformation Cost

Change library → Everything below resets → Identity rebuilds from scratch
Change scroll  → Only internal state changes → Identity barely perturbed

This explains:
- Why enlightenment is rare (requires library-level jump)
- Why habits persist (scroll-level cycles are cheap)
- Why identity crisis happens (shelf/series change forced without rebuild)

