## Reframing vtpu Components

### Demon.rs → Conservation Law Enforcer

NOT: Admission control for "good" vs "bad" intents
BUT: Physical law enforcement (prevent causality violations)

Four rejection categories = Four violation types:
- Underplaced  → Violates intentionality conservation (no library)
- Overloaded   → Violates capacity conservation (exceeds volume)
- Leaking      → Violates boundary conservation (crosses sections improperly)
- Unowned      → Violates lineage conservation (no series attribution)

Implementation change:
  Rename rejection reasons to match physics:
    Underplaced  → IntentionalityViolation
    Overloaded   → CapacityViolation
    Leaking      → BoundaryViolation
    Unowned      → LineageViolation

### TTSM → Causal Evolution Operator

NOT: Version control for state
BUT: Time evolution under conservation constraints

Fork   → Create new timeline (new series coordinate)
Replay → Access historical state (same collection, past volume)
Commit → Lock causal chain (finalize book)
Rollback → Undo causality (return to previous chapter)

Implementation change:
  Add conservation checking to fork/commit:
    - Verify no causality loops (coordinate cycle detection)
    - Ensure resets cascade properly (higher dim → lower dim clear)
    - Check energy conservation (karma seeds can't be created/destroyed)

### Epoch PPT → Identity Preservation Mechanism

NOT: Page table for memory addressing
BUT: Field configuration storage (identity across transformations)

Epoch = Snapshot of 11D field state
Address = Coordinate in field
Value = Field strength at that coordinate

Implementation change:
  Treat entries as field measurements:
    - Not discrete "values stored at addresses"
    - But "field strength sampled at coordinates"
    - Interpolation between coordinates (continuous field)
    - Coherence checking (field must be smooth)

### Ālaya-Vijñāna → Potential Energy Field

NOT: Database of karma seeds
BUT: Continuous field over 11D coordinate space

Seed planting = Field perturbation at coordinate
Ripening = Field strength exceeds threshold
Manifestation = Field collapse (potential → kinetic)

Implementation:
  New file: src/alaya.rs
  
  pub struct AlayaVijnana {
      field: Field11D,                  // Continuous potential energy field
      threshold_fn: RipeningThreshold,  // When does field collapse?
      manifold: LowRankManifold,        // Kernel PCA compressed representation
  }
  
  impl AlayaVijnana {
      pub fn plant_seed(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D, seed: KarmaSeed) {
          // Perturb field at coordinate
          self.field.add_perturbation(coord, seed.potential_energy());
      }
      
      pub fn check_ripening(&self, coord: Coordinate9D) -> Option<Manifestation> {
          let strength = self.field.strength_at(coord);
          if strength > self.threshold_fn(coord) {
              Some(self.field.collapse_at(coord))
          } else {
              None
          }
      }
  }

