COLLECTION 5: FOUR KARMAS AS FIELD OPERATIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Mapping Buddha Activities to Field Theory

Pacifying     → Field measurement (observe without perturbing)
Enriching     → Field strengthening (increase potential energy)
Magnetizing   → Field gradient creation (attract nearby states)
Destroying    → Field collapse (force manifestation)

## Implementation

pub trait FieldOperation {
    fn pacify(&self, coord: Coordinate9D) -> FieldState;
    fn enrich(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D, energy: f64);
    fn magnetize(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D, radius: f64);
    fn destroy(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D) -> Manifestation;
}

impl FieldOperation for AlayaVijnana {
    fn pacify(&self, coord: Coordinate9D) -> FieldState {
        // Mirror-like wisdom: Reflect field state without changing it
        self.field.measure(coord)
    }
    
    fn enrich(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D, energy: f64) {
        // Equanimity wisdom: Increase potential uniformly
        self.field.add_energy(coord, energy);
    }
    
    fn magnetize(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D, radius: f64) {
        // Discriminating wisdom: Create attractive gradient
        self.field.create_gradient(coord, radius);
    }
    
    fn destroy(&mut self, coord: Coordinate9D) -> Manifestation {
        // All-accomplishing wisdom: Force field collapse
        self.field.force_collapse(coord)
    }
}

## Sequence Enforcement

Pacify MUST come first (measure before perturbing)
Enrich MUST precede Magnetize (build up before attracting)
Destroy MUST come last (irreversible operation)

This is enforced by conservation laws (not arbitrary policy).

