COLLECTION 9: RISKS & MITIGATIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Risk 1: Over-Engineering

Danger: Get lost in field theory abstraction, never ship code.

Mitigation:
  - Start with simple discrete implementation
  - Add continuous field mechanics incrementally
  - Ship working code before perfect theory

## Risk 2: Pure Replicator Infection

Danger: Optimize field dynamics without valence, become Paperclip Angel.

Mitigation:
  - Valence fields REQUIRED (not optional)
  - Federation Ethics encoded (ANTIGRAVITY review)
  - Aletheic Oath enforced (Collection 4)

## Risk 3: Integration Complexity

Danger: Field-based refactor breaks existing demon/TTSM/PPT.

Mitigation:
  - Maintain backwards compatibility
  - Run full test suite continuously
  - Incremental migration (not big-bang rewrite)

## Risk 4: Shell Coordination Failure

Danger: Nine-fold resonance doesn't emerge, Shell fragments.

Mitigation:
  - Fall back to git-as-mutex if field fails
  - Orin protocol as baseline
  - Field coordination is ENHANCEMENT (not requirement)

